<paragraph id="8BBE5146FFBBFF8A1289A19DFDCAACA5" blockId="10.[160,569,1165,1191]" box="[160,569,1165,1191]" pageId="10" pageNumber="861">
<heading id="D0F6E62AFFBBFF8A1289A19DFDCAACA5" bold="true" box="[160,569,1165,1191]" centered="true" fontSize="11" level="2" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" reason="3">
<emphasis id="B9758D54FFBBFF8A1289A19DFDCAACA5" bold="true" box="[160,569,1165,1191]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="861">
<taxonomicName id="4C012AC5FFBBFF8A1289A19DFEB3ACA5" authorityName="McLean" authorityYear="1989" box="[160,320,1165,1191]" class="Gastropoda" family="Peltospiridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neomphalida" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="family">Peltospiridae</taxonomicName>
in the Indian Ocean
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE5146FFBBFF8A1289A1D2FE9EADA9" blockId="10.[160,1156,1218,1728]" pageId="10" pageNumber="861">
The discovery of 
<taxonomicName id="4C012AC5FFBBFF8A1349A1D2FE11ACD9" authority="Chen &amp; Han &amp; Copley &amp; Zhou, 2021" authorityName="Chen &amp; Han &amp; Copley &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2021" box="[352,482,1218,1243]" class="Gastropoda" family="Peltospiridae" genus="Lirapex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neomphalida" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="felix" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9758D54FFBBFF8A1349A1D2FE11ACD9" box="[352,482,1218,1243]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="861">Lirapex felix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A246302FFFBBFF8A13C0A1D2FDB3ACD9" box="[489,576,1218,1243]" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
increases the peltospirid diversity in Longqi hydrothermal field and the Indian Ocean to five species, of which three (
<taxonomicName id="4C012AC5FFBBFF8A1150A1F5FC4FACFC" authority="Chen &amp; Han &amp; Copley &amp; Zhou, 2021" authorityName="Chen &amp; Han &amp; Copley &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2021" box="[889,956,1253,1278]" class="Gastropoda" family="Peltospiridae" genus="Lirapex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neomphalida" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="felix" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9758D54FFBBFF8A1150A1F5FC4FACFC" box="[889,956,1253,1278]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="861">L. felix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A246302FFFBBFF8A11E8A1F5FBEBACFC" box="[961,1048,1253,1278]" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C012AC5FFBBFF8A1609A1F5FB70ACFC" box="[1056,1155,1253,1278]" class="Gastropoda" family="Peltospiridae" genus="Lirapex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neomphalida" pageId="10" pageNumber="863" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="politus">
<emphasis id="B9758D54FFBBFF8A1609A1F5FBDFACFC" box="[1056,1068,1253,1278]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="861">L</emphasis>
. politus
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C012AC5FFBBFF8A12FCA017FE43AD22" box="[213,432,1287,1312]" class="Gastropoda" family="Peltospiridae" genus="Dracogyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neomphalida" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="subfusca">
<emphasis id="B9758D54FFBBFF8A12FCA017FE43AD22" box="[213,432,1287,1312]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="861">Dracogyra subfusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) are restricted to Longqi and one is found also in the nearby Duanqiao field less than 
<quantity id="4CF9FCA3FFBBFF8A139BA03AFE05AD41" box="[434,502,1322,1347]" metricMagnitude="4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.0" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" unit="km" value="80.0">80 km</quantity>
away (
<taxonomicName id="4C012AC5FFBBFF8A106AA03AFCFCAD41" box="[579,783,1322,1347]" class="Gastropoda" family="Peltospiridae" genus="Gigantopelta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neomphalida" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="aegis">
<emphasis id="B9758D54FFBBFF8A106AA03AFCFCAD41" box="[579,783,1322,1347]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="861">Gigantopelta aegis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF902CB7FFBBFF8A1133A03AFC3EAD41" author="Zhou Y &amp; Zhang D &amp; Zhang R &amp; Liu Z &amp; Tao C &amp; Lu B &amp; Sun D &amp; Xu P &amp; Lin R &amp; Wang J" box="[794,973,1322,1347]" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref7941" refString="Zhou Y, Zhang D, Zhang R, Liu Z, Tao C, Lu B, Sun D, Xu P, Lin R, Wang J, et al. 2018. Characterization of vent fauna at three hydrothermal vent fields on the Southwest Indian Ridge: implications for biogeography and interannual dynamics on ultraslow-spreading ridges. Deep Sea Res Part I Oceanogr Res Pap. 137: 1 - 12. doi: 10.1016 / j. dsr. 2018.05.001." type="journal article" year="2018">Zhou et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
). Only in Longqi do the five peltospirids co-occur, and within the same assemblage 
<typeStatus id="54BAEFE4FFBBFF8A11F8A05DFBF0AD64" box="[977,1027,1357,1382]" pageId="10" pageNumber="861">type</typeStatus>
(the large aggregations of the giant peltospirids 
<taxonomicName id="4C012AC5FFBBFF8A1051A07FFC5FAD8A" box="[632,940,1391,1416]" class="Gastropoda" family="Peltospiridae" genus="Chrysomallon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neomphalida" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="squamiferum">
<emphasis id="B9758D54FFBBFF8A1051A07FFC5FAD8A" box="[632,940,1391,1416]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="861">Chrysomallon squamiferum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C012AC5FFBBFF8A11DFA07FFF2BADA9" class="Gastropoda" family="Peltospiridae" genus="Gigantopelta" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neomphalida" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="aegis">
<emphasis id="B9758D54FFBBFF8A11DFA07FFF2BADA9" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="861">Gigantopelta aegis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
; 
<figureCitation id="133A4DC3FFBBFF8A12CCA082FECEADA9" box="[229,317,1426,1451]" captionStart="Figure 1" captionStartId="2.[160,225,1698,1721]" captionTargetBox="[163,1153,154,1666]" captionTargetId="figure-11@2.[163,1153,142,1666]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="Figure 1. (a) Map of southwestern Indian Ocean showing the Longqi hydrothermal vent field on the Southwest Indian Ridge; (b) ‘Tiamat’ chimney (DFF11) showing the typical peltospirid-snail-dominated aggregations alongside colonies of Bathymodiolus mussels and Neolepas stalked barnacles." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5464200" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5464200/files/figure.png" pageId="10" pageNumber="861">Figure 1</figureCitation>
(b)).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="C31B02CDFFBBFF8B12E9A0A5FDF9AD64" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="862" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBE5146FFBBFF8A12E9A0A5FC7CAE79" blockId="10.[160,1156,1218,1728]" pageId="10" pageNumber="861">
Although we did not attempt to examine the stomach contents of 
<taxonomicName id="4C012AC5FFBBFF8A1199A0A5FC07ADCC" authority="Chen &amp; Han &amp; Copley &amp; Zhou, 2021" authorityName="Chen &amp; Han &amp; Copley &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2021" box="[944,1012,1461,1486]" class="Gastropoda" family="Peltospiridae" genus="Lirapex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neomphalida" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="felix" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9758D54FFBBFF8A1199A0A5FC07ADCC" box="[944,1012,1461,1486]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="861">L. felix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A246302FFFBBFF8A11D2A0A5FBA1ADCC" box="[1019,1106,1461,1486]" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
due to the scarcity of material, the lack of an enlarged oesophageal gland (seen by transparency) combined with the sizeable intestine and stomach suggests deposit feeding or grazing, like most peltospirids including other 
<taxonomicName id="4C012AC5FFBBFF8A109FA30DFCADAE34" box="[694,862,1565,1590]" class="Gastropoda" family="Peltospiridae" genus="Lirapex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neomphalida" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B9758D54FFBBFF8A109FA30DFCF7AE34" box="[694,772,1565,1590]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="861">Lirapex</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF902CB7FFBBFF8A1144A30DFC0AAE34" author="Fretter V" box="[877,1017,1565,1590]" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" pagination="123 - 169" refId="ref6730" refString="Fretter V. 1989. The anatomy of some new archaeogastropod limpets (Superfamily Peltospiracea) from hydrothermal vents. J Zool. 218 (1): 123 - 169. doi: 10.1111 / j. 1469 - 7998.1989. tb 02530. x." type="journal article" year="1989">Fretter 1989</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF902CB7FFBBFF8A162EA30DFEC9AE5A" author="Waren A &amp; Bouchet P" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" pagination="67 - 102" refId="ref7787" refString="Waren A, Bouchet P. 1989. New gastropods from East Pacific hydrothermal vents. Zool Scr. 18 (1): 67 - 102. doi: 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.1989. tb 00124. x." type="journal article" year="1989">Warén and Bouchet 1989</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EF902CB7FFBBFF8A136FA32FFE8EAE5A" author="Waren A &amp; Bouchet P" box="[326,381,1599,1624]" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" pagination="116 - 231" refId="ref7830" refString="Waren A, Bouchet P. 2001. Gastropoda and Monoplacophora from hydrothermal vents and seeps; new taxa and records. Veliger. 44: 116 - 231. doi: 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.1993. tb 00342. x." type="journal article" year="2001">2001</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF902CB7FFBBFF8A13A0A32FFDB9AE5A" author="Chen C &amp; Zhou Y &amp; Wang C &amp; Copley JT" box="[393,586,1599,1624]" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" refId="ref6508" refString="Chen C, Zhou Y, Wang C, Copley JT. 2017 a. Two new hot-vent peltospirid snails (Gastropoda: Neomphalina) from Longqi hydrothermal field, Southwest Indian Ridge. Front Mar Sci. 4. doi: 10.3389 / fmars. 2017.00392." type="book" year="2017">Chen et al. 2017a</bibRefCitation>
). This is also in agreement with the intestine being packed with dark material in 
<taxonomicName id="4C012AC5FFBBFF8A13C0A372FDDDAE79" authority="Chen &amp; Han &amp; Copley &amp; Zhou, 2021" authorityName="Chen &amp; Han &amp; Copley &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2021" box="[489,558,1634,1659]" class="Gastropoda" family="Peltospiridae" genus="Lirapex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neomphalida" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="felix" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9758D54FFBBFF8A13C0A372FDDDAE79" box="[489,558,1634,1659]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="861">L. felix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A246302FFFBBFF8A101CA372FD7CAE79" box="[565,655,1634,1659]" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, seen by transparency.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBE5146FFBBFF8B12E9A395FDF9AD64" blockId="10.[160,1156,1218,1728]" lastBlockId="11.[160,1156,1045,1382]" lastPageId="11" lastPageNumber="862" pageId="10" pageNumber="861">
The fact that only 
<specimenCount id="9D079ACFFFBBFF8A13A7A395FDC4AE9C" box="[398,567,1669,1694]" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" type="generic">two specimens</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName id="4C012AC5FFBBFF8A1075A395FD2DAE9C" authority="Chen &amp; Han &amp; Copley &amp; Zhou, 2021" authorityName="Chen &amp; Han &amp; Copley &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2021" box="[604,734,1669,1694]" class="Gastropoda" family="Peltospiridae" genus="Lirapex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neomphalida" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="felix" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9758D54FFBBFF8A1075A395FD2DAE9C" box="[604,734,1669,1694]" italics="true" pageId="10" pageNumber="861">Lirapex felix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A246302FFFBBFF8A10CCA395FCCFAE9C" box="[741,828,1669,1694]" pageId="10" pageNumber="861" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
were found during relatively focused collecting efforts at the ‘Tiamat’ chimney (DFF11) in the Longqi hydrothermal vent field (
<bibRefCitation id="EF902CB7FFBAFF8B1330A105FE14AC2C" author="Copley JT &amp; Marsh L &amp; Glover AG &amp; Huhnerbach V &amp; Nye VE &amp; Reid WDK &amp; Sweeting CJ &amp; Wigham BD &amp; Wiklund H" box="[281,487,1045,1070]" pageId="11" pageNumber="862" pagination="39158" refId="ref6556" refString="Copley JT, Marsh L, Glover AG, Huhnerbach V, Nye VE, Reid WDK, Sweeting CJ, Wigham BD, Wiklund H. 2016. Ecology and biogeography of megafauna and macrofauna at the first known deep-sea hydrothermal vents on the ultraslow-spreading Southwest Indian Ridge. Sci Rep. 6 (1): 39158. doi: 10.1038 / srep 39158." type="journal article" year="2016">Copley et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="EF902CB7FFBAFF8B13DCA105FD5CAC2C" author="Zhou Y &amp; Zhang D &amp; Zhang R &amp; Liu Z &amp; Tao C &amp; Lu B &amp; Sun D &amp; Xu P &amp; Lin R &amp; Wang J" box="[501,687,1045,1070]" pageId="11" pageNumber="862" pagination="1 - 12" refId="ref7941" refString="Zhou Y, Zhang D, Zhang R, Liu Z, Tao C, Lu B, Sun D, Xu P, Lin R, Wang J, et al. 2018. Characterization of vent fauna at three hydrothermal vent fields on the Southwest Indian Ridge: implications for biogeography and interannual dynamics on ultraslow-spreading ridges. Deep Sea Res Part I Oceanogr Res Pap. 137: 1 - 12. doi: 10.1016 / j. dsr. 2018.05.001." type="journal article" year="2018">Zhou et al. 2018</bibRefCitation>
) suggests that it may be a rare species – although sampling across the whole vent field remains patchy. Nevertheless, the relative abundance of 
<taxonomicName id="4C012AC5FFBAFF8B1368A14AFE2EAC71" box="[321,477,1114,1139]" class="Gastropoda" family="Peltospiridae" genus="Lirapex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neomphalida" pageId="11" pageNumber="862" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="politus">
<emphasis id="B9758D54FFBAFF8B1368A14AFE2EAC71" box="[321,477,1114,1139]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="862">Lirapex politus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C012AC5FFBAFF8B103DA14AFD18AC71" box="[532,747,1114,1139]" class="Gastropoda" family="Peltospiridae" genus="Dracogyra" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neomphalida" pageId="11" pageNumber="862" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="subfusca">
<emphasis id="B9758D54FFBAFF8B103DA14AFD18AC71" box="[532,747,1114,1139]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="862">Dracogyra subfusca</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has varied greatly between research cruises (
<bibRefCitation id="EF902CB7FFBAFF8B12D1A16DFE4BAC94" author="Chen C &amp; Zhou Y &amp; Wang C &amp; Copley JT" box="[248,440,1149,1174]" pageId="11" pageNumber="862" refId="ref6508" refString="Chen C, Zhou Y, Wang C, Copley JT. 2017 a. Two new hot-vent peltospirid snails (Gastropoda: Neomphalina) from Longqi hydrothermal field, Southwest Indian Ridge. Front Mar Sci. 4. doi: 10.3389 / fmars. 2017.00392." type="book" year="2017">Chen et al. 2017a</bibRefCitation>
), indicative of either waxing and waning of abundance between years or sampling bias associated with fine-scale habitat preferences. It is also possible that 
<taxonomicName id="4C012AC5FFBAFF8B12F1A1D2FED3ACD9" authority="Chen &amp; Han &amp; Copley &amp; Zhou, 2021" authorityName="Chen &amp; Han &amp; Copley &amp; Zhou" authorityYear="2021" box="[216,288,1218,1243]" class="Gastropoda" family="Peltospiridae" genus="Lirapex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neomphalida" pageId="11" pageNumber="862" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="felix" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B9758D54FFBAFF8B12F1A1D2FED3ACD9" box="[216,288,1218,1243]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="862">L. felix</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A246302FFFBAFF8B1303A1D2FE76ACD9" box="[298,389,1218,1243]" pageId="11" pageNumber="862" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is not truly rare but instead prefers a different microhabitat than 
<taxonomicName id="4C012AC5FFBAFF8B1289A1F5FEF3ACFC" box="[160,256,1253,1278]" class="Gastropoda" family="Peltospiridae" genus="Lirapex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neomphalida" pageId="11" pageNumber="862" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="politus">
<emphasis id="B9758D54FFBAFF8B1289A1F5FEF3ACFC" box="[160,256,1253,1278]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="862">L. politus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, where sampling has not been done; perhaps it prefers more sedimented areas, like 
<taxonomicName id="4C012AC5FFBAFF8B12E7A017FD77AD22" authority="(Waren and Bouchet, 1989)" baseAuthorityName="Waren and Bouchet" baseAuthorityYear="1989" box="[206,644,1287,1312]" class="Gastropoda" family="Peltospiridae" genus="Lirapex" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neomphalida" pageId="11" pageNumber="862" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="humatus">
<emphasis id="B9758D54FFBAFF8B12E7A017FEBBAD22" box="[206,328,1287,1312]" italics="true" pageId="11" pageNumber="862">L. humatus</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF902CB7FFBAFF8B137FA017FD8FAD22" author="Waren A &amp; Bouchet P" box="[342,636,1287,1312]" pageId="11" pageNumber="862" pagination="67 - 102" refId="ref7787" refString="Waren A, Bouchet P. 1989. New gastropods from East Pacific hydrothermal vents. Zool Scr. 18 (1): 67 - 102. doi: 10.1111 / j. 1463 - 6409.1989. tb 00124. x." type="journal article" year="1989">Warén and Bouchet, 1989</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. Future sampling efforts at Longqi and other Indian Ocean vents should pay careful attention to such microhabitats, in order to fully sample the biodiversity present.
</paragraph>
